**commercial use, commercial development, commercial
distribution, or provision of the Software as part of a
commercial service is legally prohibited** without a separate
written commercial license from the licensor.

## 1. Permitted Use

The following uses are expressly permitted under this license:

- Personal study, research, experimentation, evaluation, and
  hobby projects, without any anticipated commercial
  application.
- Internal, noncommercial activities of charitable, educational,
  public-research, public-safety, public-health, environmental,
  or governmental organizations.
- Noncommercial citation and demonstration of the Software in
  academic papers, technical blog posts, and educational
  materials.
- Viewing the source code, forking the repository, and
  submitting noncommercial contributions (Pull Requests) on a
  public code-hosting platform.

## 2. Prohibited Use

The following acts are prohibited without the licensor's prior
**express written consent**. Any violation of this Section
immediately terminates all of your licenses (see the
"Violations" clause above), and the licensor reserves the right
to pursue any and all legal and monetary remedies available
under applicable copyright and other laws.

1. **Commercial Use** - Any direct or indirect for-profit
   activity, or any internal operations supporting a for-profit
   activity, including (without limitation) operating the
   Software in a paid product or service, deploying it as an
   internal operations tool of a for-profit entity, or
   distributing it to employees as a productivity tool of a
   for-profit entity.
2. **Commercial Distribution** - Distributing the Software or
   any derivative work thereof to a third party, whether for a
   fee or free of charge, as the whole or any part of a product
   or service, including (without limitation) any paid SaaS,
   managed service, OEM offering, consulting deliverable, or
   bundled distribution.
3. **Commercial Development of Derivative Works** - Developing
   any derivative work (including forks, modifications, and
   rebranded versions) based on the Software with the intent
   to integrate, port, or re-implement it in a commercial
   product or commercial service.
4. Removing, altering, or obscuring this license, the copyright
   notice, or the "Required Notice" above.
5. Sublicensing or transferring any of your licenses under
   these terms.

## 3. Commercial License

If you require commercial use, commercial development, or
commercial distribution rights, you must enter into a separate
